*Steps*

* Set up a Eucalyptus 3.4.1 Cloud
* Enable LDAP synchronization to create account, users and groups:
{code}
# euca-lictool --password password --custom atliens-v2.lic --out atliens-quota.lic
# euca-modify-property -f authentication.ldap_integration_configuration=atliens-quota.lic
{code}
* Add key to an admin of an account and a user of an account.  For example:
{code}
# euare-useraddkey --as-account account4 -u admin
# euare-useraddkey --as-account account4 -u user31
{code}
* Apply account-level policy:
{code}
[root@odc-c-06 ~]# euare-accountlistpolicies -a account4 --region eucalyptus-admin@ -v
ec2-deny-vmtypes
